question: Which country was the location of the event "Transition to the New Order"?
explanation: Indonesia was the location of the event "Transition to the New Order". Indonesia's transition to the New Order in the mid-1960s, ousted the country's first president, Sukarno, after 22 years in the position. One of the most tumultuous periods in the country's modern history was the commencement of Suharto's 31-year presidency.
